name: Antique Style B&B with Patio in Center
description:
Spacious and bright B&B in a historical warehouse building in Amsterdam City Center, with private entry, bathroom & patio.

The B&B is newly renovated and refurbished in a lovely antique style.

The apartment is very centrally located; only 5 mins walk to central station and Dam Square. It is close to shops, bars, restaurants, museums, public transport and all that you need!

reg: 0363 8C4B 95AE A74F 3FE6
neighborhood_overview:
You will be staying in the heart of the historical center of Amsterdam, near the Singel on the Canal Belt. You will find many (traditional) bars, cafes, coffeeshops, restaurants and shops on your door step. Within minutes you are on Dam Square (where the Royal Palace and the New Church are located), at the Anne Frank Museum or Amsterdam Museum, at the flower market, in the famous 'Jordaan' area, at the 'Nine Streets' shopping area, in the Haarlemmerstraat, Chinatown, or red light district. The Amsterdam museum district (where the Rijks, Stedelijk and Van Gogh Museums are located) and entertainment/theatre districts Rembrandtplein and Leidseplein, are also easy to reach in about 15 min walk or short tram or bike ride.

The apartment is close to everything that Amsterdam center has to offer! We will share our tips and favourites of Amsterdam with you!

name: Spacious/ near centrum/ self check-in
description:
Your ideal budget getaway in Amsterdam!

✨ Great location - in the most cosmopolitan and trendy neighborhood of Amsterdam - de PIJP, next to CENTER.

✨Area bustling with the best restaurants, small cafes, cool bars, shops, street market

✨ Public transport just around the corner - 1 stop tram or subway to the old city, canals, museums.
neighborhood_overview:
"De Pijp" is one of the most popular neighborhoods of Amsterdam – cozy but yet cosmopolitan, trendy and diverse. This artistic area is full of fantastic cafes, lunchrooms, bars and coffee shops. As for restaurants -there is a wide selection of ethnic and exotic food to choose from - French, Italian, Turkish, Thai, Moroccan, Indian, Surinamese, Caribbean, Japanese and much more.
Shopping is also great in the small boutique stores all around us.

In the middle of trendy De Pijp area is one of the nicest parks in Amsterdam – Sarphatipark.

The city’s most famous outdoor market is here - Albert Cuypmarkt. It attracts thousands of visitors every day, and with over 300 stalls you can find there anything - food, flowers, clothes, furniture, art...

Heineken brewery (Heineken Experience) is here as well. Heineken's rich and successful history has been presented in their old defunct brewery with several amusement park attractions added to the exhibit.

description: Welcome to our spacious 2-bedroom apartment! Enjoy the comfort of an extra-large 180x220 cm bed, a generous living area, a kitchen, and shower. neighborhood_overview:
Oosterparkbuurt is a lively and diverse neighborhood in Amsterdam, known for its vibrant atmosphere, historic architecture, and beautiful green spaces. At the heart of the area lies Oosterpark, a spacious urban park where locals gather to relax, exercise, and enjoy community events. The neighborhood is filled with charming cafes, international restaurants, and unique boutiques, making it a popular choice for those who appreciate a dynamic yet welcoming environment.

Oosterparkbuurt is also exceptionally well-connected to the rest of Amsterdam. With a direct metro line, you can reach the city center in just 5 minutes, making it easy to enjoy all the attractions and amenities of central Amsterdam while still enjoying the community feel of a residential neighborhood. This combination of convenience, culture, and green space makes Oosterparkbuurt a highly desirable place to live.
host_about: We are a professional property management company operating throughout Amsterdam, dedicated to providing guests with an excellent experience. Most properties in our portfolio are privately owned, allowing us to offer an unique and authentic local stay. We’re always happy to share local recommendations to help guests make the most of their time in the city.

name: Authentic Farmhouse The Vergulden Eenhoorn 1
description:
There is great history behind the hotel. The Vergulden Eenhoorn was established in 1702 as a city farm and used to be one of very few farmhouses the city of Amsterdam has.

Together with the city of Amsterdam the farmhouse was fully renovated to modern standards, while maintaining the historic value and its features.

The space is fully equipped with all necessities to make your stay as comfortable as possible!
neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam East is a very populair neighborhood. The hotel and restaurant are a stones throw away from the Amstel Canal, where you can go for a nice walk or visit one of the bars and restaurants with water side views. Within a 10 min walk you will find park Frankendael and other hotspots of Amsterdam East.
host_about: Amsterdam host with a few lovely b&b rooms and apartments in the heart of the city. Born and raised in Amsterdam I love welcoming guests from all over te world. Feel free to contact me!

name: Private loft, free parking at central Vondelpark!
neighborhood_overview:
Close to the Vondelpark, typical dutch houses, nice ambiance, friendly neighbors. Lots of nice restaurants, pubs and local stores & markets. All the museums, restaurants and terraces are open again.

If you are looking for more tranquil options, you could visit the little fisherman villages like Volendam and Edam. Maybe a round of golf in the area and have beautiful walks or bike rides.

My home is also near to the highway and a great location to venture into all areas around Amsterdam. Visit Utrecht, The Hague, Delft or Den Bosch beautiful historical cities, ALL within 1hr.

Or for the kids there are many attractions around aswell, beach, sailing, horse riding, attractionpark Duinrell, Legoland Discovery Centre, all within 1hr.

description:
WELCOME

This beautiful, cosy and artistic apartment with two balconies and a home office, is just outside the city center of Amsterdam.

Conveniently surrounded by many shops, perfect access to public transport and close to different city parks, while only 15 mins from Schiphol Airport.

You will feel at home and love this place!
neighborhood_overview:
This artistic apartment is situated in Amsterdam West, in the Bos en Lommer area. It is comfortable, light, clean and very conveniently located.

There are 3 supermarkets within 100-meter distance, as well as an organic food shop, a market (Wed & Sat), plenty of lunchrooms and restaurants, and everything else you need (bakery, butcher, fish shop and flower shops) in the street.

Also, the place is close to 3 parks: Rembrandtpark, Erasmuspark and Westerpark, where you can go for a walk and grab a drink. In Westerpark you find many bars, restaurants and events.

description:
The Superstay is a boutique guest room with ensuite bathroom on the 3rd floor at the rear and is completely private and quiet.

You can drop of your bags from 11.30 AM

4minutes walk to the Rijksmuseum/vanGogh museum.
2 min walk: Heineken Experience, Albert Cuijp Market& boattours

The room is situated in the very trendy and popular district:
De Pijp/Quartier Latin, full of cafes, restaurants and terraces, in the middle of Amsterdam.

Very easily accessible with public transportation. 1 stop from Rai
neighborhood_overview:
The Superstay is a Boutique Guestroom (completely private) located in the bustling heart of Quartier Latin, right in Amsterdam, with the Museumplein around the corner.
All major tourist attractions are close to the Superstay, such as the Heineken Experience, boat trips, the Albert Cuijp market, and the Museum Square. The beautiful canals are a short walk away. Vondelpark and Leidseplein are 10 min walk.

The area where you stay is very vibrant, multicultural and full of restaurants, pubs and sunny terraces. Behind the Albert Cuijpmarkt is a beautiful park where you can walk or picnic, as the locals do.
In the side streets of the Ferdinand Bolstraat, 100 meters away from the Superstay, you will find beautiful boutiques and fashion shops.

The Superstay can be reached very easily by public transportation: tram and metro. By metro you are within 10 minutes from Central Station and 1 stop by metro from the Rai congress center.

description: Romantic 2-bedroom apartment (50m2) in the heart of Jordaan, one of Amsterdam's oldest neighborhoods. Surround yourself with authentic architecture and canal houses. Just steps away, you'll find the vibrant Saturday market, where locals gather for fresh produce and artisanal delights. An ideal spot to savor local culture. Book this city gem for your stay. neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is one of the oldest and most idyllic neighborhoods in Amsterdam with its authentic architecture and beautiful (canal) buildings. You will be staying on a side street of the Westerstraat and near the Noordermarkt. An absolute hotspot when you book a holiday in the capital. Dive into the Jordaan for the many old cafes, various restaurants, and unique (delicatessen) shops.

On Mondays and Saturdays, there is a very pleasant and busy market on Westerstraat, Lindengracht, and Noordermarkt. All tourist attractions are within walking distance or can be reached by bicycle, which is easy to rent nearby. The Anne Frank House is just 500 meters away, and the Central Station is within walking distance.

name: Cute apartment in the lovely Pijp area!
description:
My lovely apartment is located in De Pijp — a lively and trendy neighborhood filled with restaurants, bars, shops, the RAI, the Albert Cuyp Market, the popular Museumplein, and Sarphatipark. This area is the place to be when you’re in Amsterdam.

All the best spots are within walking distance. There’s also a tram stop nearby, as well as a metro station that takes you from South to North in just minutes.
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to De Pijp.
It’s one of the older neighbourhoods of Amsterdam. It has a lot of nice coffee places to go, trendy boutiques, shops and bars.

De Pijp is brimming with fantastic (typical Dutch) cafés, restaurants, coffee shops and bars. Of course, a visit to Amsterdam wouldn’t be the same without a trip to the famous Albert Cuypmarket, flanked by over 100 shops. If you wander down Albert Cuypstraat, Gerard Doustraat and Ferdinand Bolstraat, the main streets in de Pijp, you'll find many exotic and authentic Syrian, Moroccan, Surinamese restaurants, to name but a few, and a typical Amsterdam pub is located on almost every corner. Also in abundance are the Islamic butchers, Surinamese, Spanish, Indian and Turkish delicatessens and grocery stores.

It's easy to find your way in this area!

description:
Stay in an apartment next to Vondelpark and just a 10-minute walk from Museumplein while enjoying all the conveniences of the Catalonia Vondel Amsterdam hotel. This 80 m² apartment features 2 bedrooms, a fully equipped kitchen, a bathroom, and a living room with a sofa and Smart TV. neighborhood_overview:
You’ll be staying in the vibrant Oud-West district, an up-and-coming area with a growing array of activities and services in recent years. Most buildings were constructed in the early 20th century, and today it’s one of the city’s most bohemian neighborhoods, with designer shops, brunch spots, and specialty coffee houses, as well as a wide range of entertainment options.

Leidseplein, just 350 meters from the hotel, is the nightlife hub of the neighborhood, with restaurants, bars, nightclubs, cinemas, and theaters. This area of Amsterdam also features artisan and gourmet food markets at the cultural space De Hallen. Not to mention that the city’s green lung, Vondelpark, is just 300 meters away, offering 47 hectares, including the Openluchttheater, an open-air theater hosting free performances every summer.

neighborhood_overview:
AMSTERDAM – EASTERN ISLANDS

Where water and modern architecture meet
Surrounded by glistening water on all sides, the Oostelijke Eilanden (Eastern Docklands) are a delight to behold. As the Maritime Museum (Scheepvaartmuseum) recalls the sea pioneers of the past, their adventurous spirits live on in its original modern architecture and historic warehouses repurposed into contemporary hotspots.



AMSTERDAM CENTRUM - CITY CENTER + CANAL DISTRICT
In addition to the world-famous historic Canal Ring, Amsterdam's City Centre district ('Centrum') is home to a host of renowned museums, charming and high-end shopping areas, fantastic culture and entertainment.

Amsterdam’s renowned art and culture and top shopping
In Amsterdam’s centre you will, of course, find the magnificent Canal Ring, but there is so much more besides. The inner city, for instance, is bursting with interesting museums, sometimes hidden behind beautiful canal-side faça

name: Catalonia Vondel Amsterdam 4* - Premium room
description: Experience a superior stay in the Premium Rooms at the Catalonia Vondel Amsterdam hotel, featuring a cozy minimalist design and a private bathroom. Take advantage of all the amenities the hotel offers, such as 24-hour reception, daily housekeeping, or a buffet breakfast, as well as a restaurant and gastropub where you can dine or enjoy a drink whenever you like. All of this in one of the best areas of Amsterdam, near the famous Vondelpark and the lively Leidseplein Square.
neighborhood_overview:
You’ll be staying in the vibrant Oud-West district, an up-and-coming area with a growing array of activities and services in recent years. Most buildings were constructed in the early 20th century, and today it’s one of the city’s most bohemian neighborhoods, with designer shops, brunch spots, and specialty coffee houses, as well as a wide range of entertainment options.

Leidseplein, just 350 meters from the hotel, is the nightlife hub of the neighborhood, with restaurants, bars, nightclubs, cinemas, and theaters. This area of Amsterdam also features artisan and gourmet food markets at the cultural space De Hallen. Not to mention that the city’s green lung, Vondelpark, is just 300 meters away, offering 47 hectares, including the Openluchttheater, an open-air theater hosting free performances every summer.

description:
Get an unique Amsterdam experience and easily explore Amsterdam like a local.
It's a home away from home, or 'gezellig' as the Dutch would say.
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located on the Kinkerstraat, on the corner with the Bilderdijkstraat and near the Jordaan, on the 5th floor with the canal belt, the 9 Streets and the city center behind. The shopping offer of the Bilderdijkstraat is therefore also around the corner, as is the daily Ten Katemarkt and the cultural center De Hallen. For relaxation, you can cycle to the Vondelpark in a few minutes and also to the Westerpark you can cycle directly via the Bilderdijkstraat.

Women only

—-

The area is Westerpark, only 5 minutes walk from the famous UNESCO JORDAAN area. Anne Frank House is a 20 minutes walk.

The Museum District (Museumplein) is a 10 minutes tram ride from here. The tram stop is 2 minutes from the apartment.

For people coming by car or motorbike, there is a free and enclosed parking at a 15 minute drive from the boat.

On the deck of the houseboat, you can sit in the sun and have a fantastic view over the Keizersgracht and you can wave to the tourists who sail past in boats.

neighborhood_overview:
IJburg is a charming, safe and mostly residential neighbourhood which is especially popular for those who enjoy modern architecture and urban design. It's also a perfect location for water sports enthusiasts with options for kayaking, hiking, cycling, windsurfing and paddle boarding amongst others. The area offers a range of cafes, restaurants and bars for those looking for somewhere to enjoy a quiet drink.

During the summer there are two small local beaches including a beach club to enjoy in the summer months, as well as several nature spots where you can walk or cycle and take in the scenery.

You can jump off the boat for a swim or take a walk along the water to IJburg beach which is just 2km away. The city centre is just a 15 min tram ride away from our ship.

name: Unique apartment in Amsterdam's Jordaan district
description: This chic apartment is located in one of Amsterdam’s most trendy and historically rich neighborhoods. Live like a local; with local neighborhood markets around the corner,  many good restaurants, cafes and shops at a walking distance, but close to the buzzing city, museums and other tourist attractions.
neighborhood_overview:
Situated on the canal, in one of Amsterdam's trendiest neighborhoods. Jordaan is a district in the city center of Amsterdam, originally a working-class neighborhood, but it has now become one of the most expensive, upscale locations of the city. It is known for its beautiful 17th-century houses, popular bars, restaurants, street markets, art galleries, designer boutiques and original shops. The Jordaan is clustered between the four canals of Prinsengracht, Lijnbaansgracht, Passeerdersgracht and Brouwersgracht, on the west side of Amsterdam’s main ring of canals (called the grachtengordel). When in Amsterdam, it is a must to stroll through the little streets and canals.
Every Saturday there is the Lindengracht Market, around the corner of the apartment, with amazing flowers, food and local specialties. It is within walking distance of all the famous tourist attractions, such as the Amsterdam canals, Nine Streets (shopping area), the Anne Frank House, The Dam, Leidse Square and Am

description:
Stay in this bright apartment at the Catalonia Vondel Amsterdam hotel, excellently located just 300 meters from Vondelpark and Leidseplein. The apartment features a spacious living room with Smart TV, and Chromecast, a kitchen, and a bathroom with a washing machine. Additionally, you’ll enjoy all the conveniences of a hotel, including daily housekeeping, 24-hour reception, and an optional buffet breakfast.

neighborhood_overview:
You’ll be staying in the vibrant Oud-West district, an up-and-coming area with a growing array of activities and services in recent years. Most buildings were constructed in the early 20th century, and today it’s one of the city’s most bohemian neighborhoods, with designer shops, brunch spots, and specialty coffee houses, as well as a wide range of entertainment options.

Leidseplein, just 350 meters from the hotel, is the nightlife hub of the neighborhood, with restaurants, bars, nightclubs, cinemas, and theaters. This area of Amsterdam also features artisan and gourmet food markets at the cultural space De Hallen. Not to mention that the city’s green lung, Vondelpark, is just 300 meters away, offering 47 hectares, including the Openluchttheater, an open-air theater hosting free performances every summer.

Shopping center Boven 't Y is within walking distance, with well-known shopping chains such as H&M, Decathlon, Hema & Albert Heijn, but also the necessary craft shops. Throughout Amsterdam-Noord you can find hip restaurants & bars, such as: Pompet, Il Pecorino, Cannibale Royale, the Goudfazant, Oedipus Brewery, Pllek, IJver and Loetje aan ’t IJ. Home to some of the world’s best art museums, Oud-Zuid (Old-South) is one of Amsterdam’s most elegant and well-heeled neighbourhoods, where impressive manors line leafy streets, and chic boutiques abound. From the splendour of Museumplein to the vibrant Vondelpark and the serene boulevards of Willemspark, the beautiful neighbourhood of Oud-Zuid rewards the visitor at every turn.

Just outside the cultural heart of Amsterdam lies the posh neighbourhood of Oud-Zuid, with its ravishing villas and tranquil curving streets. The Oud-Zuid is arguably the elegant heart of Amsterdam, and is definitly the city’s most prestigious cultural district.

Amsterdam’s elegant Oud-Zuid (Old-South) was developed over a century ago as a cultural gateway to the city, at the tip of what was previously a boggy polder. Just a short tram ride south of Centraal Station takes you into one of the most cosmopolitan and vibrant districts of Amsterdam. Welcome to de Pijp.

De Pijp is brimming with fantastic cafés, restaurants, coffee shops and bars. Of course, a visit to Amsterdam wouldn’t be the same without a trip to the Albert Cuypmarket, flanked by over 100 shops. If you wander down Albert Cuypstraat and Ferdinand Bolstraat, the main streets in de Pijp , you'll find many exotic and authentic Syrian, Moroccan, Surinamese restaurants, to name but a few, and a typical Amsterdam pub is located on almost every corner.

Also in abundance are Surinamese, Spanish, Indian and Turkish delicatessens and grocery stores.

name: Romantic ‘Aft Cabin’ on Board of an Icebreaker
description: Please be welcome on our unique houseboat, a former East-German icebreaker, tug, pusher and fire boat built in 1954. We ourselves live in the front part, the aft cabin – the former crew bunks - we converted into a cozy little studio with a vintage feel. neighborhood_overview:
The Borneo-island is a peninsula in the Eastern Harbour District. An area known for its architecture and urban planning. You can take beautiful walks in a decor of history, contemporary architecture and typical Dutch harbour landscape.
20 minutes from the busy city center you will find peace and wide views over the water. Children still play on the streets because there is little traffic. When the weather is nice residents quickly come outside to sit on the sidewalks with a drink and a bite, having a chat with their neighbors. It is a jovial and cosy neighborhood where it’s still normal to great each other. In summertime people cool down in and on the water, with a SUP (which you can rent down the block), canoes and small boats, and of course it's wonderful to take a swim in the natural water, and the cold water lovers even swim whole year round.

name: ★NEW: CANAL VIEWS ★ CREATIVE TOUCH ★ JORDAAN ★
description:
This unique & Stylish 2BR apartment offers the perfect base for exploring Amsterdam from a very central location.

Entrance on the ground floor where you will find an open kitchen and dinging space, next to a spacious lounge and some working spaces.

One floor up, you find the two bedrooms, a bathroom and a sunny balcony!

All amenities are included, prepare for the trip of a lifetime!
neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is possibly the most famous neighbourhood in the Netherlands. Akin to the reputation enjoyed by London’s Cockneys, this once working-class bastion was renowned for tight community bonds, radical politics and a love for drink and over-the-top sing-a-longs. Gentrification of decades past has attracted more galleries, restaurants, specialty shops and upwardly-mobile residents to its scenic streets but there’s undeniably still a distinct atmosphere to be enjoyed here.

The Jordaan begins at Brouwersgracht, just west of the Amsterdam Central Station and arches around the western side of Canal Ring between Prinsengracht and Lijnbaansgracht before ending at Leidsegracht. The area north of Rozengracht is a more ‘touristy’ and commercial section, although the quieter area to the south is no less scenic.

Very centrally located, a hidden gem in a prime location. Get an unique Amsterdam experience and easily explore Amsterdam like a local.
You stay here on a child-friendly dead end street with only local traffic.

neighborhood_overview:

You will experience unprecedented peace and space, while you can drive onto the A10 ring road within 5 minutes and cycle to the cozy Oud-Zuid in 5 minutes. name: Apartment with balcony, quiet street, trendy area
description: I love my bright, top-floor apartment, and I hope you will too! The huge window in the ceiling fills the kitchen-living room with light. The quiet, leafy street is full of potted plants and bicycles. My favourite time to relax on the roof terrace is at the end of the day, with the windmill against the sunset. The neighbourhood is a great choice for a stay in Amsterdam – shops, bars, cafes and restaurants, away from the touristy areas but easy by tram to the city centre.
neighborhood_overview: I’m in the nicest part of the area called the Indische Buurt. The quiet streets of late 19th-century buildings run parallel to the Javastraat, which I think is the nicest, most authentic shopping street in Amsterdam! It’s a total mix – shops with fruit and vegetables spilling out onto the street, cafes from trendy to traditional, creative restaurants, boutiques, bakers, fishmongers, Yemeni and Syrian street food, and a great Italian delicatessen. It’s a short walk to the lively Dappermarkt market, the Oosterpark and Tropenmuseum. Artis Zoo is a little further. The canal area, main museums, and Dam Square are all around 25 minutes by public transport, and quicker by bike.
host_about: I’m a Political Science Masters’ student at the University of Amsterdam. I’ve grown up in Amsterdam bilingual English and Dutch, so I’ve always felt international. I love to travel, whether for pleasure or study. I’m lucky enough to live in a lovely apartment in a great neigbourhood, and for limited periods it’s available on Airbnb.

name: Canalview Suite BnB Amsterdam | Balcony+Kitchen
description: Welcome to our private Amsterdam canal suite, nestled in a beautifully restored historic canal house. Enjoy amazing canal views from your top-floor haven in Amsterdam Old-South. The suite features a full kitchen, balcony, and personalized service including daily housekeeping, a detailed guidebook, tea, coffee, welcome treats, and other delightful touches you will love. Only 10-20 minutes from the center or Museum Square, it's an ideal authentic getaway. Perfect for groups and families of 4!
neighborhood_overview: We are situated in a lively area of Old-South at the Schinkel Canal on the top floor of our lovingly restored canal-side house. There are many restaurants and cafes within walking distance, all loved by locals and expats alike. A highlight is an active bridge in front of our BnB. Sit in the Cafe next to the canal and watch the spectacle with a hot or cold beverage! A true feeling of local Amsterdam.
host_about:
Hi there, Paul and Karen here!
Our story started in the hotel and travel sphere some time ago, and as you can see, we never left. Just like we did not leave Amsterdam. Loving to share and being passionate hosts, it has been our pleasure to welcome guests to our Amsterdam BnB for more than 2 decades. Always taking care of our guest's experience and needs together, we would love to welcome you to Amsterdam as well. A personal and warm welcome is always provided, but besides that, you will not notice us, though you can always reach us – we live on the premises with our two cats Rosie and Billy, in the mornings often joined by a Grey Heron, who we love to feed. We feel that doing good is important, we are committed to good causes and are active in different charity projects. An exciting but tough change to our life we are currently pursuing: removing plastic from our everyday life, step by step.
Hope to hear from you soon!
Paul and Karen

description: Noorderbed is a family-friendly B&B where you can unwind after a busy day in Amsterdam. neighborhood_overview: Noorderbed is in Amsterdam-Noord, a district that is vigorously developing after decades of being left behind. All ferries are free of charge (including for cyclists).

description:
Welcome! Stay in lovingly furnished apartments – a personal alternative to impersonal hotel rooms or unfamiliar private rentals. Our suites combine the quality standards of a hotel with the coziness and comfort of your own apartment.

neighborhood_overview: In the Dutch capital, art and culture lovers get their money's worth! Our accommodation in Amsterdam Hemonystraat is located right in the heart of the alternative De Pijp district! This is the perfect place to relax and explore the city's wide range of art and culture. In the narrow streets of this hip district you will find a variety of traditional bars and nice cafés. Just a few metres from the largest inlet of the Amstel, you'll find yourself at the ideal starting point for an unforgettable visit to Amsterdam. The charm of the typical alleys and picturesque bridges makes almost every heart beat faster. So it's no surprise that you can also reach the city's most important sights within a few minutes on foot, by bike or a short boat trip.
host_about: At limehome, we believe that everyone deserves a better place while travelling. A place to look forward to return to. Simply a place designed to stay®. Our digital-enabled guest journey without a physical reception and staff on-site makes your stay more convenient.

name: Perfect location apartment, pijp
description: A stylish apartment located in the heart of the Pijp, the most popular area in Amsterdam, near the Museum District and Leidseplein. Marie Heinekenplein is within walking distance as well as the well-known Albert Cuypmarkt. De Pijp is also known for its cozy restaurants, cafes and trendy boutiques. There are many cultural facilities nearby such as Rijksmuseum and Van Gogh. The centre of Amsterdam, Leidseplein, the Canal area and the Vondelpark can be reached within a few minutes by bike or walk.
neighborhood_overview:
De Pijp is brimming with fantastic (typical Dutch) cafés, restaurants, coffee shops and bars. Of course, a visit to Amsterdam wouldn’t be the same without a trip to the famous Albert Cuypmarket, flanked by over 100 shops. If you wander down Albert Cuypstraat and Ferdinand Bolstraat, the main streets in de Pijp, you'll find many exotic and authentic Syrian, Moroccan, Surinamese restaurants, to name but a few, and a typical Amsterdam pub is located on almost every corner. Also in abundance are the Islamic butchers, Surinamese, Spanish, Indian and Turkish delicatessens and grocery stores.

It's easy to find your way in this area!

name: Quiet scape by the metro
description: Enjoy a peaceful stay just steps from Gaasperpark, with nature all around and the metro to Amsterdam just a 5-minute walk away. The apartment features 2 bedrooms a fully equipped kitchen, renovated bathroom, sunny balcony, and a cozy workspace. Jumbo supermarket nearby for all your needs. neighborhood_overview:
Nestled at the edge of Gaasperplas Park, our home offers the perfect mix of city access and peaceful nature. Wake up to birdsong, stroll through tree-lined paths, or cycle along scenic routes surrounded by green fields and canals. We provide bikes so you can explore beyond the city—ride through local farmlands, follow river trails, or head to Abcoude, a postcard-perfect Dutch village just 15 minutes away by bike with its cafés, cheese shops, and historic charm.

This area is ideal for families and nature-lovers. Pack a picnic or a yoga mat and spend a slow morning at the park. There are playgrounds, open spaces for the kids, and plenty of quiet corners for rest and reflection.
And with Gein metro station just a 5-minute walk away, you’re seamlessly connected to central Amsterdam while still feeling a world apart.

name: Unique spacious (private) boat in Amsterdam.
description:
"Sailing barge Titaan” is a relatively new ship in the Dutch fleet. She is build in 2001 and has been used mostly for romantic sailing trips and weddings.

Nowadays she has been refitted to accommodate groups of passengers (up to 12 people). The traditional white sailing barge in combination with a more modern and luxury interior gives the whole ship an interesting twist and a perfect place to unwind and relax.
neighborhood_overview:
The ship is moored in the marina of IJburg. Characteristic of IJburg is that it's located on an archipelago of artificial islands in the IJmeer. As a result, the ship is right next to (or should we say in) the IJmeer, and makes you simply a few minutes away from beautiful nature reserves. The swamp forest 'Diemer Vijfhoek' is a well-known one, where the alternation of wetlands, open water and reed lands make it a true bird paradise. You can walk here from the boat in 20 minutes.

Fort Island Pampus is a stone's throw from the venue. The ferry service to Pampus departed just around the corner.

Craving an adventure a bit more far away? Polder IJdoorn and Vuurtoreneiland are located slightly to the north of the location and can be reached via Zeeburg. Here you can walk beautifully and enjoy the unique flora & fauna.

Still looking for the crowds? Amsterdam is less than 20 minutes away.

name: Cosy Apartment in De Pijp
description: Cosy home in beautiful De Pijp, with 1 bedroom and a sofa bed. The home is fully equipped, homely and perfectly located. It is 1 minute from the metro, and Albert Cuypmarkt market. De Pijp is one of the trendiest areas in Amsterdam, full of boutiques, shops, cafes and bars. Museumplein is also around the corner with the Rijksmuseum and Van Gogh Museum. Great amounts of public transport on the doorstep.
neighborhood_overview:
De Pijp, a residential neighborhood situated in the south part of Amsterdam, is one of the city’s most hip and trendy areas, bursting with cozy cafes, diverse restaurants and a lively nightlife. From the beautifully landscaped gardens of Sarphatipark to the famous Albert Cuypmarkt street market, Quartier Latin (de Pijp) is the place to be.
De Pijp is home to the country's largest open-air market, the Albert Cuypmarkt. The market boasts numerous vendors, from clothes, accessories and flowers to fresh seafood, dutch cheese, vegetables and the famous stroopwafels.
The Museumplein is also just around the corner with the Rijksmuseum, the Stedelijk and Van Gogh Museum. Within a few minutes cycling you are in the Vondelpark.

Visit the Rijksmuseum, where masterpieces by Rembrandt, Vermeer, and other Dutch Golden Age artists await. The nearby Van Gogh Museum is a tribute to the life and work of the famed painter, while the Stedelijk Museum showcases a diverse range of modern and contemporary art. Each of these venues offers a unique experience, making Museumplein a cultural epicenter.

The neighborhood itself is as inviting as its museums. The expansive square is a popular gathering spot, perfect for a leisurely picnic, an afternoon with the family, or simply soaking up the energy of the city. name: Riverbridge Suite - Historic Center Canal District
description:
Take an early morning stroll and enjoy the nearby famous Rijksmuseum & Van Gogh Museum, without the tourists. Wander around the historic canals while the city sleeps, then head back for a morning coffee at my unique Dutch-styled suite, perfectly situated in the Amsterdam Canal District, close to many attractions.

Riverbridge Suite is the perfect location for a short or long stay in Amsterdam, where you will have all the comforts of home.
neighborhood_overview:
The central canal district in Amsterdam is a must-visit destination for anyone who loves beautiful architecture, fascinating history, and vibrant culture. With its network of winding canals and stunning 17th century buildings, the district is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and a true gem of the city.

As you stroll along the cobbled streets and waterways, you'll be enchanted by the elegant gables and arched bridges that line the canals. You'll also have the opportunity to visit world-class museums and galleries, such as the Van Gogh Museum and the Rijksmuseum, which showcase some of the greatest works of art from around the world.

In the central canal district, you'll also find a wide variety of restaurants, cafes, and shops that offer something for everyone. From traditional Dutch food and beer to international cuisine and designer clothing, you'll be spoilt for choice. And at night, the district comes alive with live music, theaters, and clubs that offer an excitin
host_about:
As an Australian who has lived in the UK, Holland, and many other places, I have a passion for traveling and experiencing new cultures. My work in technology has given me the opportunity to see the world and meet fascinating people from all walks of life.

But for me, travel isn't just about checking off bucket-list destinations or taking social-media-worthy photos. It's about connecting with others and providing them with a great time. Whether I'm exploring a new city with friends, sharing a cup of coffee with locals, or hosting a dinner party at my apartment, I love bringing people together and making sure they have a memorable experience.

description:
This centrally located and tastefully decorated hotel room is located in a monumental canal building in the Jordaan. The accommodation is located around the corner from the Prinsengracht, Anne Frankhuis, Westerkerk and the 9 streets. Ideally located to discover the old town!

The accommodation is located in the heart of the Jordaan, the cozy, Amsterdam village in the city center with its exciting artstudios, quirky shops and authentic Amsterdam bars and cafes. We can only say it right away: parking on the Egelantiersgracht is impossible. Forget it, you're in the heart of the Jordaan. The good news is that it's super easy to reach by public transportation.

The accommodation is less than 1 km from the Anne Frank House. The property is 17 minutes walk from the Royal Palace Amsterdam and 1.6 km from the Flower Market. The property is 2 km from Rembrandtplein and 1.6 km from Leidseplein.
host_about: Hello from Amsterdam! We are a small, happy family consisting of myself, my husband Steven, our adorable baby girl Ella, and our furry baby Jopie. neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam Zuid is one of the most posh and desirable residential neighborhoods in Amsterdam with the city's most fashionable shopping streets: PC Hooftstraat, Van Baerlestraat and Beethovenstraat.

You can find here also the most famous museums (Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum, Stedelijk Museum), Coster Diamonds, Concertgebouw, and the Vondelpark. Almost all streets in this part of Amsterdam Zuid are named after Dutch rivers or waterways. Many of its buildings had been built in the style of the Amsterdam School, which is a famous and beautiful architecture style. Just around the corner, not even a minute walk from the apartment, there is this sweetest and nicest coffee bar you can have. The staff is lovely and their coffee is to die for! They also serve breakfast and lunch. There are 5 supermarkets in the vicinity along with a lot of other shops. Good restaurants and bars are widely available here, just a couple of minutes away!
host_about:
I'm a consultant in The Netherlands. I enjoy travelling and meeting new people, different cultures and cuisines.

I also rent out my apartment, a beautiful home, away from home.
Enjoy one of the most beautiful views that Amsterdam has to offer in my fully equipped apartment.

name: Luxury studio incl. bikes. Close to De Pijp & RAI
description:
New and stylish studio in the south of Amsterdam, within walking distance of the popular neighborhood 'de Pijp' and only a few minutes travel distance from the center of Amsterdam and the Zuidas. Exhibition and conference center 'RAI' 350 meters away.

Two bicycles can be used free of charge.
neighborhood_overview:
The accommodation is very conveniently located: the Rivierenbuurt is a quiet area, but if you fancy a bit more excitement, you will find it within walking distance. Numerous bars and restaurants can be found in the vicinity of the property. The Scheldestraat and Maasstraat are both popular streets filled with places for a snack or a drink. Whether for breakfast, lunch or dinner. You will also find all essential shops there, such as: supermarket, bakery, butcher, greengrocer, pharmacy, cheese shop, drugstore, liquor store, caterer, etc.

De Pijp is also nearby; you get there by public transport or in a 15-minute walk. As a tourist you can indulge yourself there; next to the popular Albert Cuyp market you will find countless nice bars and restaurants there. neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to Amsterdam Oost, a vibrant and diverse neighborhood that has something for everyone. Whether you're a history buff, a nature lover, or a foodie, you'll find plenty to love here. It's a great place to experience a different side of the city, away from the tourist crowds of the city center.

When it comes to cafes and restaurants, Amsterdam Oost has some of the best in the city. Whether you're in the mood for a cozy neighborhood cafe or a trendy brunch spot or even Michelin star restaurant, you'll find plenty of options here. Some of our favorites include Coffee Bru, Rum Baba, Restaurant Wilde Zwijnen, Restaurant de Tros, De Plantage and Cafe Kuiper.

One of the must-see attractions in Amsterdam Oost is the Tropenmuseum, a fascinating museum that explores the cultures and histories of non-western societies.

And let’s not forget Artis, the city's oldest zoo. With its beautiful gardens and diverse collection of animals, Artis is a great place to

LOCATION

name: Unique Historic Private apt. | 2BR | 4P
description:
Indulge in a truly unique stay at our private top-floor apartment nestled within a 350-year-old house.

This charming abode features two serene bedrooms, a cozy living space with a convenient kitchenette, and a bathroom boasting both a shower and bath.

Immerse yourself in the authenticity of the surroundings, ensuring a distinctive and memorable experience.

Get ready for a journey of a lifetime in the heart of history!
neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam Noord is at the moment according to Skykenner the 7th trendiest neighborhood of the world. That is because of the festivals, the giant flee market, the new restaurants, the new film museum and all the artist who have their studios here.

The most agreable thing of our neighborhood is the calmness and the green with all the flowers!

There are two ferryboats who will bring you in 5 minutes to the Central Station if you get fed up with the quietness.

A very good idea is to rent a bike. The dike where we live is a very picturesque road with all kinds of wooden and brick stone houses. The oldest are build in the 17th century. The dike borders on the Vliegenbos, an untamed and very quiet wood, where you also can find the tennis loans.

An in- and outdoor swimmingpool you can find at a distance of two kilometers, if you follow the dike to Buiksloot. Most people of the north of Amsterdam however go for a swim in the lakes of the national park

neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam Oost, also known as Amsterdam East, is a vibrant and diverse neighborhood that is worth exploring for anyone visiting the Dutch capital. This area is full of hidden gems that are often overlooked by tourists, but offer a unique and authentic Amsterdam experience.

OOSTERPARK
One of the must-see attractions in Amsterdam Oost is the beautiful Oosterpark. This park was designed by the famous Dutch landscape architect, Leonard Springer, and opened in 1891. It is the perfect place to relax and enjoy nature, with plenty of green spaces, ponds, and walking paths. During the summer months, the park hosts a variety of festivals and events, including music con- certs and outdoor movie screenings.
Oosterpark

neighborhood_overview:
This part of the city was built at the end of the 19th century for the Amsterdam harbour workers. Today it is a lively and quiet neighbourhood. It is famous for the architectural style called "Amsterdam School" which was born one block away from our house. There is a very worthwhile museum around the corner about this variety of "Art Nouveau".

By bicycle (to rent just around the corner) it takes 12 minutes to get to the central station. The fantastic Westerpark is a 5 minute walk away and the beautiful shopping area called Haarlemmerstraat is less than 15 minutes walk away.

The flat is situated on the ground floor and is therefore suitable for disabled people.

Some examples of the distances from our house by bike:

25 mins to the Rijksmuseum
15 mins to Dam Square (palace)
10 mins to Central Station
35 mins to the airport (by car or public transport)

name: Big Houseboat in Amsterdam with comfortable Garden
description: Welcome aboard our spacious houseboat! Spread over 2 floors, it comfortably accommodates 4 people with 2 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms. On the garden side there is a large sliding door to a large garden with picnic table and fixed barbecue. On the waterfront there is another sliding door to a floor where to enjoy a breakfast in the sun and on the water. Perfectly located in a park and a quiet neighborhood and close to local attractions.
neighborhood_overview:
The houseboat is located together with 10 other boats hidden in a car-free green strip on Willem de Zwijgerlaan. On the waterfront you have a view of the oldest distribution center in Amsterdam. Here, all fresh products for restaurants and shops in Amsterdam are sold. A real eye-catcher is the huge mural of Keith Haring on the side of the former cold house on the property. The work of 12 by 15 meters is Haring's second largest existing mural in public space in Europe. From the houseboat you also have a view of this mural.

Within a radius of 500 m there are a number of supermarkets and an evening shop that is open daily until 1 o'clock at night. There are also plenty of restaurants and cafes where you can eat and/or drink.

At 10 minutes walk you have the Ten Katemarkt (day market) with adjacent De Hallen.

The famous Jordaan(neighborhood) with every Saturday the Noordermarkt is 20 minutes walk from the houseboat.

name: Albert Cuyp III A Studio Amsterdam
description: Modern studio apartment, housing up to two people in Amsterdam’s Pijp district, overlooking the vibrant Albert Cuyp Market.
neighborhood_overview:
The accommodation can be found south of the historical centre, lining one of the country’s most famous market streets. Existing over a 100 years, the Albert Cuypmarkt attracts a diverse crowd and enjoys a bustling yet laid back atmosphere, making it the perfect introduction to typical Amsterdam life. This animated attraction is located in the Pijp quarter, renowned for its multicultural population and its multitude of friendly bars, cafes and restaurants, providing more ethnic eateries than any other part of the city.


The studio is superbly placed for discovering Amsterdam’s stunning Canal Belt and its equally picturesque river, the Amstel. Accessible on foot in a matter of minutes, this elegant waterway hosts several cultural venues along its banks, including the Royal Carre Theatre and the Hermitage Museum. The capital’s famous Dam Square can be reached on foot in half an hour or by tram in less than fifteen minutes.

host_about:
I live in this lovely floating house with my two kids. 
In my work, I focus on regenerative practices, changemaking, and biodiversity with the aim to (re)connect people with the planet.
I feel privileged that I am purposeful in my work and live in a way that aligns with my values. My dream was to live in Amsterdam, in a community that supports each other to live consciously and sustainably and this became real. I hope this will inspire you.

name: Cozy apartment in De Pijp
description:
The apartment is located in a quite street of the centre of De Pijp, behind the Heineken brewery. The main attractions like Dam Square, the Rijkmuseum, Museumplein and the centre are at a walking distance.
The apartment is at the first floor and it has a bedroom, a kitchen, a big bathroom and a typical Dutch living room with Van Gogh vibes.
The apartment is good for couples, limited group of friends or a family.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in the De Pijp area of Amsterdam, where most streets in are named after Dutch painters, like Jan Steen, Frans Hals, Ruysdael and Vincent van Gogh. It is located behind the Heineken Brewery (nowadays a local tourist attraction) and the Albert Cuyp Market, one of the most known markets in Amsterdam.
Next to it, there is Marie Heinekenplein square, which has a number of bars and cafes. Along the canal Ruysdaelkade, there is also a small red-light district.

About De Pijp: it is densely populated and has a diverse population, with a relatively high percentage of highly educated people and people living alone. Notable people to have lived in De Pijp include painter Piet Mondriaan.

name: Cozy family home Amsterdam, close to city center
description: Our house is located in the Nieuwendam district, a unique green place in the lively Amsterdam North. The house is great for families or a quiet group of friends (28+), who want to relax after a day in the city, and who don't mind occasionally feeding our two lovely cats. The kids can play in the park across the street. The bus stops at the end of the street and takes you to the metro in 8 minutes. Or grab the bike to one of the Old Dutch villages nearby!
neighborhood_overview:
If you want to see Amsterdam from a side that has not yet been discovered, you have to come to Amsterdam-Noord. Get your bread on Purmerplein at the bakery, or dine at Lazuur, and how about homemade cakes and cacke at Liever. All within walking distance of our home.
Or grab the bike to Durgerdam, Broek in waterland and Holysloot, where time seems to be standing still. You will be given a glimpse into how one used to live. Bicycle along the farmer where you can buy fresh milk and eggs and children can cuddle the calves.
From our house you can take the bike over the Nieuwerdammerdijk to the central station, which will take you 15 minutes. Along the way, you can drink a beer at café Het Sluisje, the oldest cafe in Amsterdam Noord.
Our house is surrounded by greenery; the Schellingewouderbreek with its rich flora and fauna or take a refreshing dip in Het IJ near the Rietlanden.

neighborhood_overview:
Schinkelbuurt is a charming and romantic neighborhood in Amsterdam, located in the Zuid district. Nearby you’ll find cosy cafés, a variety of restaurants, supermarkets and The Vondelpark. All to find at 2 min walking distance.

There’s Dignita, a hip little brunch place with a social conscience that gives victims of human trafficking the chance to start a new life and learn a new trade making delicious, sophisticated food like these zucchini fritters. There’s the Vondeltuin; a lovely play area for kids. There’s Ron Blauw: a Michelin star restaurant. There’s a local bakery as well as pizzeria’s and Thai food restaurants. It’s also recommended to stroll through the beautiful Oranje Nassaulaan with it’s magnificent villa’s and nineteen century big houses.
host_about:
Hi! We’re Jelle and Lysan, a couple living in Amsterdam. Jelle works as a real estate agent, and I (Lysan) work at a marketing agency. We have two sons, Steiner (9) and Daan (6)

Our home, recently renovated in 2022, spans two floors and is located in the beautiful Zuid neighborhood, just a minute’s walk from Vondelpark. We are respectful and tidy individuals and always take great care when staying in someone else’s property. Regards Lysan &Jelle

Jordaan
The Jordaan is possibly the most famous neighbourhood in the Netherlands. Akin to the reputation enjoyed by London’s Cockneys, this once working-class bastion was renowned for tight community bonds, radical politics and a love for drink and over-the-top sing-a-longs. Gentrification of decades past has attracted more galleries, restaurants, specialty shops and upwardly-mobile residents to its scenic streets but there’s undeniably still a distinct atmosphere to be enjoyed here.

Around the corner is the famous Anne Frank House, you'll find yourself immersed in the rich cultural heritage of Amsterdam. The area is steeped in history, with picturesque canals and quaint streets waiting to be explored.

name: Stunning canal view place
description: Welcome to my gem in Amsterdam’s beloved Jordaan district. This is a super authentic and cozy bedroom apartment offers an enchanting location and a lot of attention to detail that captures the essence of this historic city. While you stay at my place I will make sure you have all my top insider recs for exploring this amazing neighbourhood and beyond
neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is a historic neighborhood in Amsterdam, known for its picturesque canals, charming streets, and cultural significance. It's located in the city center, just to the west of the central train station. The neighborhood is characterized by its narrow houses with gabled facades, many of which date back to the 17th century. It has been given unesco status in 2010

Jordaan has a rich history and was originally a working-class area. Today, it's a trendy and desirable place to live, with a vibrant community and a mix of boutiques, cafes, art galleries, and restaurants. It's also famous for its weekly markets, like the Noordermarkt, and its proximity to the Anne Frank House.

The neighborhood has a relaxed, bohemian atmosphere and is a great place to explore on foot or by bike. It's a cultural hub with many art studios and music venues, making it a beloved area for artists and musicians.

neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is a picturesque neighborhood in Amsterdam, renowned for its narrow streets, charming canals, and historic buildings. Located west of the city center, the Jordaan was originally a working-class area, but has since transformed into one of the city's most desirable and trendy neighborhoods.

Characterized by its cozy, village-like atmosphere, the Jordaan is a maze of narrow alleys and hidden courtyards, lined with independent boutiques, art galleries, and a diverse array of cafes and restaurants. The area is particularly famous for its traditional Dutch "brown cafes," where locals and visitors alike gather for drinks in a warm, convivial setting.

The Jordaan's cultural significance is highlighted by several notable landmarks, including the Anne Frank House and the Westerkerk, a stunning 17th-century church with a prominent bell tower offering panoramic views of the city. neighborhood_overview: Our limehome is located in the middle of the lively Leidseplein neighbourhood. From here, you can easily reach all the main sights of the floating city on foot. In addition to the cultural attractions, you will also find popular bars, restaurants and theatres where street artists and local talent delight their audiences. Right on your doorstep is the Amsterdam canal belt, a system of canals that is considered exemplary architecture of the Golden Age and has earned Amsterdam the nickname Venice of the North. Thanks to its proximity to the Museum Quarter, you can also reach impressive city highlights such as the Rijksmuseum or the entrance to the Vondelpark in just a few minutes. The Leidseplein and Prinsengracht tram stops are less than a 5-minute walk away, where a dedicated bus line will even take you directly to Schiphol Airport. All in all, you are in perfect hands here to explore the most diverse facets of the Dutch capital.

Originally a working-class district, the Jordaan is now filled with boutique shops, cozy cafés, art galleries, and canal-side terraces, all woven into a network of peaceful streets and picturesque canals.

Despite being close to major attractions, the area has a local, residential feel, and is much calmer than the tourist-heavy zones. You’ll find organic grocery stores, weekend markets, and family-run bakeries just around the corner. It's a perfect location for travelers who want to experience Amsterdam like a local on foot, by bike, or along the canals.
host_about: Couple based in AMS who accidentally became passionate hosts it started with one apartment, then turned into a slightly obsessive hobby. One of us works in strategy, the other just works on making the perfect espresso. We love thoughtful spaces, long breakfasts, and meeting travelers from around the world. Our goal? Make you feel like you’re staying at a friend’s place but with better towels and stronger Wi-Fi!

neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is a picturesque neighborhood in Amsterdam, renowned for its narrow streets, charming canals, and historic buildings. Located west of the city center, the Jordaan was originally a working-class area, but has since transformed into one of the city's most desirable and trendy neighborhoods.

Characterized by its cozy, village-like atmosphere, the Jordaan is a maze of narrow alleys and hidden courtyards, lined with independent boutiques, art galleries, and a diverse array of cafes and restaurants. The area is particularly famous for its traditional Dutch "brown cafes," where locals and visitors alike gather for drinks in a warm, convivial setting.

The Jordaan's cultural significance is highlighted by several notable landmarks, including the Anne Frank House and the Westerkerk, a stunning 17th-century church with a prominent bell tower offering panoramic views of the city. name: Amsterdam luxe woning
description: Lovely luxury spacious house on the swimming water with fantastic views in Amsterdam IJburg.
neighborhood_overview:
The house is located in the IJburg district. A beautiful new neighborhood with lots of nature and space around you. IJburg is a children-friendly neighborhood with, among other things, a city beach. In the summer there is a lot of activity on the water.

In 5 minutes you walk to the tram with which you are in the center of Amsterdam in 15 minutes.

There are several nice restaurants, shops and a beautiful harbor within walking distance where you can have a drink and eat at various restaurants on the terrace.

You can also rent bicycles at the bike shop and enjoy cycling in nature.

Welcome to Hotel Espresso, a true Amsterdam treasure for tourists and business travellers of the world. Located ideally in Amsterdam’s Old West district, the Vondelpark, The Van Gogh and Rijks Museums, as well as the Leidseplein, with its many restaurants and clubs, are all within walking distance. The iconic Albert Cuyp Market, just a short walk away, offers an immersive experience into Amsterdam's vibrant street life, showcasing an array of fresh produce, artisanal goods, and colorful stalls.

Culture aficionados will delight in the proximity to renowned attractions such as the Rijksmuseum and Van Gogh Museum, where masterpieces from Dutch masters await exploration. name: Cute appartement in peaceful area near city centre
description: Our house was built in the 1920’s for working class people and was designed by the famous Berlage School. The north of Amsterdam has changed immensely since then and in our neighborhood, you will now find the coolest new restaurants, bars and clubs. Alongside peaceful parks, a little forest and a bike ride away from the characteristic country dike houses. The nearest metro is a 5-minute walk away and the ferry that takes you right into the city centre is a 5-minute bike ride (15 minute walk).
neighborhood_overview:
Food:
Fromagerie Kef, the best French and Dutch cheese, van der Pekplein
Bakkerij Solinger, the very best sourdough bread, NDSM Plein 27
Chateau Karlito, good nature wines, van der pekstraat 27
There is a simple market in the shopping centre Mosveld (2 minute walk) every Wednesday, Friday and Saturday.

Restaurants
Hotel de Goudfazant, a classic and all-time favorite,
Barracuda, new trendy fish restaurant,
Café Keppler, nice for breakfast and easy lunch,
Klaproos, fun and easy pizza place,
Pompet, nice place in the park perfect for kids,
Europizza, upmarket pizza place on a strip with bar next to it

Things to do:
Bicycle to NDSM in the morning to buy fresh bread at Bakkerij Solinger.
Bicycle from the Niewendammerdijk to Durgerdam. You will be amazed by the dike houses and country side.
Have a picknick in the Noorderpark around Pompet.
And of course, go into the centre :)

description:
•⁠ ⁠Bright, modern apartment with fully equipped kitchen, dining area & cozy balcony
•⁠ ⁠Spacious living room with streaming TV, perfect for relaxing after city adventures
•⁠ ⁠Two stylish bedrooms & two full bathrooms—ideal for families or small groups
•⁠ ⁠Located in central Amsterdam, walk to major attractions, cafes & shops

neighborhood_overview:
You'll be staying in the heart of Amsterdam-Zuid, a vibrant and authentic neighborhood loved by locals for its mix of culture, calm, and convenience!
•⁠ ⁠Fantastic location on Rijnstraat, a lively street with everything you need at your doorstep—bakeries, supermarkets, cafes, bike rentals, and local boutiques.
•⁠ ⁠Steps from Café Vrijdag—a cozy local spot perfect for brunch or evening drinks—and the popular Venster 33, known for its creative cocktails and laid-back vibe.
•⁠ ⁠Walking distance to Martin Luther Kingpark and the scenic Amstel River—perfect for a morning jog, riverside picnic, or renting a canoe on sunny days.
•⁠ ⁠Only 10 minutes by bike or tram to De Pijp, home of the iconic Albert Cuyp Market, trendy bars, and a world of international cuisine.
•⁠ ⁠A short ride to Museumplein, where you can explore the Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum, and Concertgebouw—a must for art and music lovers!
•⁠ ⁠Need groceries or essentials? You're covered with Al

neighborhood_overview:
The home is located in the beautiful residential area Amsterdam Zuid, next to museum district. It's in a part of Amsterdam where there are broad streets, nice people, shopping areas, restaurants, parks, markets and good transport around the corner to the city center. It's like a pleasant little village in the city. It's ideal for families with kids.

In the next street there is a playground for children.
There is a supermarket in our street and in the next street you will find restaurants (Chinese, iItalian, bistro), cafe's, all kinds of shops (clothing stores, Rituals and a really nice bookstore), Rolling Sushi, coffee company and nice bakery's.

In 6 minutes you walk to the Beatrix Park, a nice and quiet park with a playground for the children. The Vondelpark is a 15 minutes walk.
In 10 minutes you can walk to the famous museumplein where you will find the Van Gogh Museum, Rijksmuseum (Rembrandt) and Stedelijk museum.

neighborhood_overview:
De Baarsjes is a vibrant and dynamic neighborhood in Amsterdam West, known for its diversity, trendy cafes and restaurants, and a mix of historic and modern architecture. The area is located west of Amsterdam's city center and is well-connected by public transportation, including trams and buses. Cycling is a popular way to get around thanks to well-laid-out bike paths. The neighborhood also has easy access to the A10 highways, making it ideal for drivers.

De Baarsjes is renowned for its multicultural population and lively community. This is reflected in the variety of dining options, shops, and cultural events held throughout the year. There is a strong neighborhood community that prides itself on its inclusive and welcoming atmosphere.

neighborhood_overview: The Grachtengordel West, or Western Canal Belt, in Amsterdam is a picturesque and vibrant neighborhood that embodies the charm and history of the city. This area is characterized by its iconic canals, lined with beautifully preserved 17th-century canal houses that exude classic Dutch architecture. The streets are bustling with a diverse mix of boutique shops, art galleries, trendy cafes, and cozy restaurants, offering a blend of modern amenities and historic charm. The neighborhood is known for its lively atmosphere, with locals and tourists alike enjoying leisurely strolls along the canals, scenic boat rides, and the vibrant cultural scene. Despite its central location, Grachtengordel West maintains a serene and quaint ambiance, making it a desirable place to live and visit.

neighborhood_overview:
The house is located in one of the most charming neighborhoods of Amsterdam, Oud-West. The lively and vibrant atmosphere is at your fingertips, with the city center and the Jordaan just a few minutes away by bike. The area boasts various hotspots, including De Hallen, where you can enjoy a meal followed by a movie. Within a few minutes' walk, you'll find a variety of cozy spots like De Binnenvisser, Druis, Meatless District, The Breakfast Club, and Panache.

Looking for fresh market products? The daily Ten Kate Market, offering a wide range of fresh produce, is just a stone's throw away. There's also plenty for children to enjoy, with a petting zoo, paddling pool, and playground nearby. The Vondelpark is only a five-minute bike ride away.

The immediate vicinity offers numerous tram and bus stops, making it easy to reach all parts of Amsterdam quickly due to the central location of this home in the West district.

neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood surrounding the Westermarkt in Amsterdam is a captivating blend of rich history, vibrant culture, and modern sophistication. Nestled in the heart of the city's UNESCO-listed Canal Ring, this area offers a unique combination of old-world charm and contemporary urban living, making it one of Amsterdam's most desirable locales.

At the core of the neighborhood is the iconic Westermarkt square, dominated by the majestic Westerkerk, Amsterdam's tallest church tower. The toll of its bells has been a comforting presence for centuries, resonating through the cobbled streets and the elegant canals that weave through the area. The Westerkerk itself is a masterpiece of Dutch Renaissance architecture, and its tower offers breathtaking panoramic views of the city, drawing both locals and tourists alike.

neighborhood_overview:
Discover Muiderlaan, Amsterdam

Muiderlaan is a vibrant, modern neighborhood in Amsterdam’s IJburg district, known for its striking architecture, waterfront living, and relaxed atmosphere. Surrounded by canals and close to the IJmeer, it offers stunning water views and plenty of outdoor activities, including walks along the marina and relaxing at the city beach, Blijburg. The area features trendy cafes, diverse restaurants, and unique boutiques, creating a lively yet peaceful vibe. With excellent public transport connections, including direct trams to Amsterdam Central Station in just 20 minutes, Muiderlaan blends urban convenience with a tranquil, coastal lifestyle — a perfect retreat for work or leisure

Whether you’re a history buff, a foodie, or a lover of green spaces, Amsterdam Oost offers something for everyone.

Here’s why it’s the perfect place to stay during your visit to the Dutch capital.

neighborhood_overview:
Our apartment is located in the heart of the Jordaan, one of Amsterdam’s most beloved and charming neighborhoods. Originally a working-class district, the Jordaan is now filled with boutique shops, cozy cafés, art galleries, and canal-side terraces, all woven into a network of peaceful streets and picturesque canals.

Despite being close to major attractions, the area has a local, residential feel, and is much calmer than the tourist-heavy zones. You’ll find organic grocery stores, weekend markets, and family-run bakeries just around the corner. It's a perfect location for travelers who want to experience Amsterdam like a local on foot, by bike, or along the canals.
host_about: Couple based in AMS who accidentally became passionate hosts it started with one apartment, then turned into a slightly obsessive hobby. One of us works in strategy, the other just works on making the perfect espresso. We love thoughtful spaces, long breakfasts, and meeting travelers from around the world. Our goal? Make you feel like you’re staying at a friend’s place but with better towels and stronger Wi-Fi!

neighborhood_overview:
MUSEUMPLEIN
Amsterdam's gem is the 19th century Museum Square. It is the nexus of Dutch cultural heritage and home of the National Concert Hall (Concertgebouw) and three world-famous museums: the Rijksmuseum, the Stedelijk Museum and the Van Gogh Museum. The Museumplein has two memorials to the victims of World War II and is often used as a site for national celebrations.

VONDELPARK
The city’s beautiful and most popular park welcomes more than ten million visitors a year, and is loved by locals for dog-walking, jogging, or just a breath of fresh-air. The Vondelpark was designed by a father-and-son team of landscape architects in classic English style and was awarded national heritage status. The park now supports around 100 plant species and 127 types of trees.

neighborhood_overview:
Our apartment is located in the heart of the Jordaan, one of Amsterdam’s most beloved and charming neighborhoods. Originally a working-class district, the Jordaan is now filled with boutique shops, cozy cafés, art galleries, and canal-side terraces, all woven into a network of peaceful streets and picturesque canals.

Despite being close to major attractions, the area has a local, residential feel, and is much calmer than the tourist-heavy zones. You’ll find organic grocery stores, weekend markets, and family-run bakeries just around the corner. It's a perfect location for travelers who want to experience Amsterdam like a local on foot, by bike, or along the canals.
host_about: Couple based in AMS who accidentally became passionate hosts it started with one apartment, then turned into a slightly obsessive hobby. One of us works in strategy, the other just works on making the perfect espresso. We love thoughtful spaces, long breakfasts, and meeting travelers from around the world. Our goal? Make you feel like you’re staying at a friend’s place but with better towels and stronger Wi-Fi!

•⁠ ⁠Surrounded by trendy cafes, concept stores, yoga studios, and cozy brunch spots like Little Collins and Scandinavian Embassy—local favorites for a reason!
•⁠ ⁠A short walk to the beautiful Sarphatipark, an ideal place to unwind with a coffee or have a picnic under the trees.
•⁠ ⁠Just minutes by bike or tram to Museumplein, where you can explore the Van Gogh Museum, Rijksmuseum, or take photos at the iconic “I amsterdam” sign.

neighborhood_overview:
The area offers a unique mix of cultural vibrancy, local charm, and a peaceful retreat from the tourist-heavy center while remaining well-connected to the rest of Amsterdam.

Why Amsterdam Oost?
Amsterdam Oost is an increasingly popular district that perfectly blends the city’s rich history with modern innovation.

It’s a multicultural, trendy neighborhood brimming with lush green spaces, fascinating museums, diverse cuisine, and a laid-back vibe.

While central Amsterdam can sometimes feel overcrowded, Oost provides a quieter and more authentic experience, making it an excellent base for exploring the city.

Highlights of Amsterdam Oost

1. Proximity to the City Center
Amsterdam Oost is just a short tram or bike ride away from the city center. With excellent public transport connections, you can easily visit iconic attractions like the Anne Frank House, Rijksmuseum, or Van Gogh Museum, all within 15–30 minutes.

neighborhood_overview:
Dam Square has had a turbulent history. Around 1270 a damn was constructed in this spot in the river Amstel. Dam Square was once the central marketplace of Amsterdam where literally everything under the moon was sold.

The Royal Palace and the Nieuwe Kerk Amsterdam are also situated at Dam Square. Other nearby highlights are the red light district, the narrowest house in Amsterdam at Singel 7 and our most luxurious shopping mall 'de Bijenkorf"

Within 5 minutes by foot you enter the Jordaan Area. Jordaan is one of the most famous neighbourhoods of Amsterdam. Known for its iconic beauty and charm, the area is also home to popular attractions like Anne Frank House, the cheese museum and Noordermarkt.

If you want to see the Amsterdam you know and love from photos – flower-lined canals, quaint narrow streets and trendy boutiques, a visit to Jordaan is a must.

neighborhood_overview:
You'll be in the heart of Amsterdam’s historic canal district with charm, culture, and local life just outside your door!

•⁠ ⁠Unbeatable location right on Amstelveld, one of the most picturesque and peaceful squares in the city, home to a charming weekly flower market on Mondays.
•⁠ ⁠Just around the corner from the iconic Utrechtsestraat – a beloved local street lined with boutique shops, artisan bakeries, wine bars, and cozy cafés. Don’t miss a morning croissant from Patisserie Kuyt or a coffee at Bocca Coffee!
•⁠ ⁠Walking distance to major attractions like Rembrandtplein, Rijksmuseum, Hermitage Amsterdam, and the Royal Theatre Carré, yet tucked away in a quiet residential pocket that feels like a hidden village within the city.
•⁠ ⁠A short walk or scenic canal bike ride to the famous Albert Cuyp Market in De Pijp and Museumplein with the Van Gogh and Stedelijk Museums.

name: Studio aan het IJ
description:
Privacy in bright, modern studio on quiet street in the popular Eastern Docklands near the city center with use of patio. No kitchen, but kitchenette with fridge, Nespresso, milk frother, kettle and egg cooker. Clean modern bathroom with shower and toilet. Please note: the studio has high ceilings, and you sleep on a mezzanine without headroom accessible by stairs. Not recommended for people with limited mobility.
Outdoor swimming within walking distance. 2 bicycles included.
neighborhood_overview:
Originally a harbor area, later via frayed edge to a residential area with water on all sides. We have a small shopping mall and restaurants and bakeries within walking distance. With the free ferry from Azartplein (3 minutes by bike), you can cross over to hip Noord with many nice restaurants, entertainment venues and a cinema.
In various places, you can (at your own risk) swim in open water. With tram 7 or 26 (7 or 10 minutes' walk) you can be in the city center in no time. With the free bicycles available, this quiet neighborhood is an ideal, centrally located base.
